name: Royal Canadian Air Force CF-188B Hornet Close Up Departure from Calgary
description:
Always great to catch a fighter jet at a civilian airport! Here we have 188937, one of several two-seater McDonnell-Douglas CF-18s the Royal Canadian Air Force has in service, starting up and taxiing out super close up, and making an ear-splitting departure off 35L. Calgary sees a few CF-18s this time of year thanks to Stampede, and I'm glad I was able to catch one of them! Hope you enjoy this close up CF-18 action, with ATC included!

Thanks for watching!

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

FLIGHT INFORMATION
Operator: Royal Canadian Air Force (RCAF/ARC)
Aircraft: McDonnell-Douglas CF-188B Hornet
Livery: Standard Grey
Engines: 2× General Electric F404-GE-400
Registration: 188937 
Route: Calgary (YYC) - Calgary (YYC)
Callsign: KUGR24
Runway used: 35L
Date filmed: July 14, 2018
Local time: 1000
